==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: kyoo͞r"ēŏs'ətē
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˌkjuəriˈɒsəti/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /%kju@ri"Qs@ti/

===Noun===
'''curiosity'''

#[[inquisitive]]ness; the tendency to ask questions, investigate, or [[explore]]
#:''Cats have a natural curiosity that sometimes gets them in trouble.''
#:''Out of curiosity, why are you wearing your shirt backwards?'' (means, "I am just wondering")

====Quotations====
*'''1956''' — [[w:Arthur C. Clarke|Arthur C. Clarke]], ''The City and the Stars'', p 39
*:"Certainly there is nothing wrong with Alvin's intelligence, but many of the things that should concern him seem to be a matter of complete indifference.  On the other hand, he shows a morbid '''curiosity''' regarding subjects which we do no generally discuss.

====Antonyms====
* [[ignorance]]

